\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as the enforcement authority for the ECIO Policy Manual across all population classes defined in Section 6.4.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall maintain independent authority over the County's information technology infrastructure,
 including the authority to take immediate system-level action to protect County assets,
 reduce liability,
 or manage operational and compliance risk.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall initiate IT-administrative corrective actions in accordance with Section 6.3.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall document enforcement decisions in the Department's system of record within twenty-four (24) hours of the action.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall refer matters to the appropriate personnel authority or legal process when the non-compliance warrants action beyond the IT Director's IT-administrative authority.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as the Local Agency Security Officer (LASO) for CJIS notification purposes under the formal sanctions process defined in Section 6.5.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
