\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Compliance with this policy is mandatory for all personnel,
 entities,
 and systems within the scope of the ECIO Policy Manual.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assessment
\series default
:
 Compliance with the enforcement,
 acknowledgment,
 and exception management requirements of this policy shall be assessed through the internal audit process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Internal Audits,
 Self-Assessment,
 and Control Testing) and the annual policy review and maturity scoring process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Annual Policy Review and Maturity Scoring).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Enforcement
\series default
:
 Non-compliance with the requirements of this policy —
 including failure to complete required acknowledgments,
 failure to cooperate with IT-administrative enforcement actions,
 or failure to document and route enforcement actions as required —
 shall be addressed through the corrective action framework defined in Section 6.3 of this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions to this policy shall be documented in writing with a business justification and approved by the County Manager in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 Oral exceptions are not valid.
 Exceptions to this policy shall not be approved by the IT Director alone,
 as the IT Director is both the enforcement authority and a subject of this policy.
\end_layout

