\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The ECIO Policy Manual is an enforceable governance instrument,
 not an aspirational document.
 Every directive expressed in mandatory compliance language ("shall" or "must") across the manual is an auditable obligation backed by the corrective action framework defined in this policy.
 This policy provides the operational mechanism through which non-compliance is identified,
 documented,
 escalated,
 and resolved —
 and through which the manual's alignment with applicable law is maintained.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
For purposes of this policy,
 references to the Department's system of record refer to the designated operational recordkeeping system for enforcement actions,
 acknowledgments,
 and exception records.
 This is distinct from the 
\series bold
Authoritative System of Record
\series default
 maintained under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Policy and Documentation Formatting Standards),
 which governs policy text.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Policy Implementation and Dissemination
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall ensure that all policies within the ECIO Policy Manual are operationalized through the following implementation requirements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Publication
\series default
:
 Upon approval of a new or revised policy,
 the IT Director shall publish the updated policy to the Departmental Knowledge Base in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Knowledge Management Policy).
 The LyX master record and its compiled PDF remain the legally authoritative source in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
;
 the Knowledge Base publication constitutes the operational distribution mechanism.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Constructive Notice
\series default
:
 Publication of a policy in the Knowledge Base constitutes constructive notice to all Information Operations personnel.
 The IT Director shall issue a written notification to all Department personnel upon publication of any new or substantively revised policy.
 For non-IT County personnel,
 constructive notice is established through the acknowledgment and training mechanisms defined in Section 6.2 and 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
