\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Enforcement Authority and IT-Administrative Actions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director maintains independent authority over the County's information technology infrastructure.
 This authority includes the right to take immediate system-level action to protect County assets,
 reduce liability,
 or manage operational and compliance risk.
 This authority exists regardless of the position,
 department,
 or employment classification of the affected party.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
IT-administrative actions are distinct from personnel-disciplinary actions.
 IT-administrative actions are imposed by the IT Director under management authority over the technology infrastructure.
 Personnel-disciplinary actions are governed by the applicable labor agreement,
 County Personnel Policies,
 or employment contract and are processed through the appropriate personnel authority.
 This policy governs IT-administrative actions directly and defines the referral mechanism for personnel-disciplinary actions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The following IT-administrative actions are available to the IT Director.
 This list constitutes the governed set of actions;
 the IT Director may also impose other operationally appropriate restrictions within the IT Director's management authority over the County's information technology infrastructure to protect County assets,
 reduce liability,
 or manage operational and compliance risk.
\end_layout

