\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Corrective action may begin at any level depending on the severity of the non-compliance,
 the frequency of the occurrence,
 the risk to County assets or operations,
 and the cumulative effect of prior non-compliance.
 The IT Director is not required to follow a sequential escalation path.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall document all IT-administrative enforcement actions in the Department's system of record within twenty-four (24) hours of the action.
 Documentation shall include the nature of the non-compliance,
 the enforcement action taken,
 the affected individual or system,
 and the notification provided to the appropriate parties.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
IT-administrative actions shall remain in effect during any dispute resolution process unless the County Manager directs otherwise or a court order requires it.
 The dispute resolution pathways defined in Section 6.4 determine whether an action was justified;
 they do not automatically stay the action.
\end_layout

